Deploying app:

1. Fork this repo.
2. Create Python2.7 application on openshift.redhat.com (try to add source code from github there)
3. Add MySQL cartridge.
4. Clone openshift repo to your local mashine (add public key on openshift beforehand).
5. Add this repo as second on your local machine (http://git-scm.com/book/en/v2/Git-Basics-Working-with-Remotes#Adding-Remote-Repositories)
6. Make changes in wsgi.py file (http://www.it-recipes.com/articles/blog/204)
7. Rename database as your openshift db name (you can see it on your app page) in itblog/settings.py
8. Push changes to openshift.
9. Connect to openshift via ssh.
10. Syncdb on the server.
python manage.py syncdb
Type data for superuser.
11. Manually install pyCAPTCHA(https://github.com/reddit/reddit/issues/485)
12. create table for it
python manage.py dbshell
+------------+-------------+------+-----+---------+----------------+
| Field      | Type        | Null | Key | Default | Extra          |
+------------+-------------+------+-----+---------+----------------+
| id         | int(11)     | NO   | PRI | NULL    | auto_increment |
| challenge  | varchar(32) | NO   |     | NULL    |                |
| response   | varchar(32) | NO   |     | NULL    |                |
| hashkey    | varchar(40) | NO   | UNI | NULL    |                |
| expiration | datetime    | NO   |     | NULL    |                |
+------------+-------------+------+-----+---------+----------------+

13. Move static to openshift folder:
python manage.py collectstatic
14. Add first article / TODO: fix this bug.

TODO: create action hooks for 7-13.

For local development:

1. Add the following environment variables to ~/.profile and source it.

ITBLOG_MYSQL_DB_NAME='itblog' && export ITBLOG_MYSQL_DB_NAME
ITBLOG_MYSQL_DB_USERNAME='my-user' && export ITBLOG_MYSQL_DB_USERNAME
ITBLOG_MYSQL_DB_PASSWORD='my-pass' && export ITBLOG_MYSQL_DB_PASSWORD
ITBLOG_MYSQL_DB_HOST='' && export ITBLOG_MYSQL_DB_HOST
ITBLOG_MYSQL_DB_PORT='' && export ITBLOG_MYSQL_DB_PORT
ADMIN_MAIL='admin@gmail.com' && export ADMIN_MAIL
ADMIN_PASS='pass' && export ADMIN_PASS
SMTP_SERVER='smtp.gmail.com' && export SMTP_SERVER
SMTP_PORT='2525' && export SMTP_PORT

ITBLOG_APP_HOST='192.168.56.110' && export ITBLOG_APP_HOST
ITBLOG_APP_PORT='8080' && export ITBLOG_APP_PORT

2. You'll also need to install MySQL and create database and user with credentials that are mentioned
(probably you'll need to install all packages commented in the bottom of requirements.txt).

3. Create python virtual environment (http://docs.python-guide.org/en/latest/dev/virtualenvs) and install requirements:
pip install -r requirements.txt

